# üéØ Main Objective: Create a Feature Breakdown Document

- [ ] 1. Create document structure
  - [ ] 1.1. Create markdown file with feature name
    ```markdown
    # Feature Name
    ```
  - [ ] 1.2. Add table of contents section
    ```markdown
    ## üìù Table of Contents
    - [Introduction](#introduction)
    - [The Plan](#the-plan)
    - [Implementation](#implementation)
    - [Testing](#testing)
    - [Reflection](#reflection)
    ```

- [ ] 2. Document introduction
  - [ ] 2.1. Add feature overview
    ```markdown
    ## Introduction
    [Brief description of what the feature does and why it's needed]
    ```
  - [ ] 2.2. List prerequisites
    ```markdown
    ### Prerequisites
    - Required knowledge/setup 1
    - Required knowledge/setup 2
    ```

- [ ] 3. Create implementation plan
  - [ ] 3.1. Break down steps
    ```markdown
    ## The Plan
    1. First major step
       - Sub-step A
       - Sub-step B
    2. Second major step
    ```
  - [ ] 3.2. Add code examples for complex steps
    ```markdown
    ### Example Implementation
    ```dart
    void exampleCode() {
      // Code with comments
    }
    ```
    ```

- [ ] 4. Document testing approach
  - [ ] 4.1. List test scenarios
    ```markdown
    ## Testing
    - [ ] Test scenario 1
    - [ ] Test scenario 2
    ```
  - [ ] 4.2. Add example test code
    ```markdown
    ### Test Example
    ```dart
    void testFeature() {
      // Test code
    }
    ```
    ```

- [ ] 5. Add reflection section
  - [ ] 5.1. Document key decisions
    ```markdown
    ## Reflection
    - Why we chose X approach
    - Performance considerations
    - Future improvements
    ```
